This box is made to look like cardboard, hence the title, but you could technically take the time to change the visuals.

You would need to, in the CSS, go to the different "background-image:" or "background" lines that appear in the different faces of the box (frontleft, frontright, backleft, backright, topleft, topright) and changes these, either to different pictures for another texture; or if you want a normal color, switch them to "background: #(hex color code of your choice)"

To change the object that pops out of the box, you need, similarly, to change the "background-image:" line in the "#workskin .cardboardbox_content_img" section.
